{"parse":{"title":"National Council on Problem Gambling (Singapore)","pageid":3639563,"revid":728404306,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>National Council on Problem Gambling</b> was set up in <a href=\"/wiki/Singapore\" title=\"Singapore\">Singapore</a> on 31 August 2005 to address <a href=\"/wiki/Compulsive_gambling\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Compulsive gambling\">problem gambling</a>, following the <a href=\"/wiki/Singapore_Government\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Singapore Government\">government</a>'s decision to legalise <a href=\"/wiki/Casino\" title=\"Casino\">casino</a> gambling and build two <a href=\"/wiki/Integrated_resort\" title=\"Integrated resort\">integrated resorts</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/Marina_Bay,_Singapore\" title=\"Marina Bay, Singapore\">Marina Bay</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Sentosa\" title=\"Sentosa\">Sentosa</a>.\n</p><p>The council is chaired by <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lim_Hock_San&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Lim Hock San (page does not exist)\">Lim Hock San</a> and has 19 members.\n</p><p>One of the main tasks of NCPG is to promote public awareness on problem gambling. In January 2006, a TV series <i>Bet Your Life</i> was launched to examine problem gambling and its effects on families and society. <sup class=\"reference plainlinks nourlexpansion\" id=\"ref_initiativeJan06\"><a class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Council_on_Problem_Gambling_(Singapore)#endnote_initiativeJan06\">[1]</a></sup>  A fund of <a href=\"/wiki/S$\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"S$\">S$</a>150,000 was also set aside for public education programmes initiated by voluntary welfare organisations.\n</p><p>To counsel and help compulsive gamblers, two hotlines are set up by <a href=\"/wiki/Institute_of_Mental_Health_(Singapore)\" title=\"Institute of Mental Health (Singapore)\">Institute of Mental Health</a> and <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thye_Hua_Kwan_Moral_Society&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Thye Hua Kwan Moral Society (page does not exist)\">Thye Hua Kwan Moral Society</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=National_Council_on_Problem_Gambling_(Singapore)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ol><li><span class=\"citation wikicite\" id=\"endnote_initiativeJan06\"><b><a href=\"#ref_initiativeJan06\">^</a></b></span>  <cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/singaporelocalnews/view/186919/1/.html\">\"Council on Problem Gambling rolls out 2 public education initiatives\"</a>. Channel NewsAsia. 6 January 2006.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Council+on+Problem+Gambling+rolls+out+2+public+education+initiatives&amp;rft.date=2006-01-06&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.channelnewsasia.com%2Fstories%2Fsingaporelocalnews%2Fview%2F186919%2F1%2F.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANational+Council+on+Problem+Gambling+%28Singapore%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ol>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=National_Council_on_Problem_Gambling_(Singapore)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ncpg.org.sg/\">Official site</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1258\nCached time: 20180909042404\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: fa